    "aesthetic": "Feed images alternate between clean studio packshots and urban lifestyle looks. BACKGROUNDS are mostly seamless off‑white or light grey sweeps (#F8F8F8, #EDEDED) and warm beige boards (#D2B48C), plus real locations like concrete pavements, steps, metro platforms and textured city walls; surfaces are flat boards, rough concrete and occasionally fabric drapes. Colour grade is clean and natural with slightly warm skin tones, true‑to‑product neutrals and controlled pops of red/blue; blacks stay rich, whites are soft rather than blown out. Styling is medium-density: lifestyle shots show full outfits but few extra props, while product frames stay prop-light with the shoe sometimes paired with a single chair, block or textured fabric; recurring props include stairs, railings, crosswalks and simple studio cubes. LIGHTING is a mix of soft natural daylight outdoors (open shade or late-afternoon sidelight) and controlled studio softboxes placed at 45°–90° for gentle, low-contrast shadows on the ground; specular highlights on leather/fabric are present but not harsh. Compositions favour low, ground-level angles, 3/4 views of the sneakers, leading lines in streets, and tight crops around the ankle/foot; carousels often mix a wide establishing shot with detail macros of textures and soles. They shoot heavily with models (feet/legs and occasional half-body), with occasional product-only shots for e-commerce and drop announcements.",
